cardMonEntry.name: cardMonEntry
cardMonEntry.description: An entry in the card monitor table. Each entry represents statistics collected on each possible slot in the system.

cardMonIndex.name: cardMonIndex
cardMonIndex.description: The card number index. Valid entries are system dependent based on the chassis type.

cardMonCellsReceived.name: cardMonCellsReceived
cardMonCellsReceived.description: The number of cells revceived by the card. Note this statistic is not maintained in high-performance mode.

cardMonCellsTransmitted.name: cardMonCellsTransmitted
cardMonCellsTransmitted.description: The number of cells transmitted by the card. Note this statistic is not maintained in high-performance mode.

cardMonCellsDropped.name: cardMonCellsDropped
cardMonCellsDropped.description: The number of cells dropped by the card.

cardMonSARReceived.name: cardMonSARReceived
cardMonSARReceived.description: The number of SAR packets revceived by the card. Note this statistic is not maintained in high-performance mode.

cardMonSARTransmitted.name: cardMonSARTransmitted
cardMonSARTransmitted.description: The number of SAR packetd transmitted by the card. Note this statistic is not maintained in high-performance mode.

cardMonSARDropped.name: cardMonSARDropped
cardMonSARDropped.description: The number of SAR packets dropped by the card.

cardMonMSIMsgs.name: cardMonMSIMsgs
cardMonMSIMsgs.description: The total number of MSI messages to and from the card. Note this statistic is not maintained in high-performance mode.

cardMonCardInsertions.name: cardMonCardInsertions
cardMonCardInsertions.description: The number of card insertions into the slot represented by the slot number.

cardMonCardRemovals.name: cardMonCardRemovals
cardMonCardRemovals.description: The number of card removals on the slot.

cpuPctUse.name: cpuPctUse
cpuPctUse.description: Current utilization of the MCP cpu. Displays the utilization of the MCP cpu as a percentage at the time the object is polled. CPU utilization is highly variable, and as such, cpuPctUse can only be considered a snap shot and may not be valid immediately after polling the object.
